━━━━ SPEC FILE 1: [feature].happy-path.spec.ts ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

Cover the normal successful user journey. Every test = one complete user action.

  MUST COVER:
  ✓ User completes the main flow from start to finish
  ✓ All UI elements (headings, buttons, inputs, tables) appear in the correct order
  ✓ Correct redirect or state change happens after each action
  ✓ Data is persisted and visible after form submission or API call
  ✓ Success messages / toasts appear and then disappear
  ✓ Authenticated-only pages are accessible when logged in

━━━━ SPEC FILE 2: [feature].edge-cases.spec.ts ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

Cover every boundary, invalid input, and unusual user behavior.

  MUST COVER:
  ✓ Submit form with ALL fields empty → correct validation messages appear
  ✓ Leave each REQUIRED field blank one at a time → field-level error shown
  ✓ Invalid email format → email error message shown
  ✓ Password below minimum length → password error shown
  ✓ Maximum length input (use INVALID_INPUTS.longString) → truncated or rejected
  ✓ Whitespace-only input → treated as empty, not valid
  ✓ SQL injection in text fields → safely handled, no crash
  ✓ XSS payload in text fields → rendered as plain text, not executed
  ✓ Duplicate entry (same email used twice) → duplicate error shown
  ✓ Double-click submit button rapidly → only one request sent
  ✓ Navigate away mid-flow then return → form state handled gracefully
  ✓ Paste text into fields (not just type) → works correctly
  ✓ Tab key navigation through form fields → correct focus order

━━━━ SPEC FILE 3: [feature].error-states.spec.ts ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

Cover everything that can go wrong on the server or network side.

  MUST COVER:
  ✓ API returns 500 → user-facing error message shown, app does not crash
  ✓ API returns 401 → user is redirected to login page
  ✓ API returns 404 → not-found state or message shown correctly
  ✓ API returns 422 (validation error) → field-level errors shown from server
  ✓ Network failure (abort) → offline/network error message shown
  ✓ Slow API response (3s delay) → loading spinner visible during the wait
  ✓ Token/session expires mid-use → session expiry handled, redirected to login
  ✓ Concurrent requests conflict → last-write-wins or conflict error shown

